cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a compact network for image classification, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of unsupervised learning and K-means algorithm for filter bank learning indicates that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed pooling method and feature selection approach suggest that it may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
